CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 28, 1959, pg. 3 reads: "Eleven-to-One - Eleven members of the University of Pittsburgh Chess Club "ganged up" on Fred Foreman and managed to come through with one win and two draws in a match held at Schenley Hall. Foreman is one of the most highly regarded chess players in the Tri-State area."
TitMainTitle: Fred Foreman playing against eleven members of the University of Pittsburgh Chess Club, in Schenley Hall
